post_cb({"20405376": {"ParentId": "20405321", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Per \u00a710.1:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_20405321_20405376_0\"><sup>1</sup> A class can be derived from any number of base classes. [<em>Note</em>: The use of more than one direct base class\n  is often called multiple inheritance. \u2014<em>end note</em> ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Everything else depends on compiler's implementation and limitations.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "952747", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "20405376", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2013-12-05T16:29:19.327", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-05T16:29:19.327"}, "20405380": {"ParentId": "20405321", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>It's implementation defined. C++11 gives recommended minimums in the <em>Implementation quantities</em> section of the standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_20405321_20405380_0\">\u2014 Direct and indirect base classes [16 384].<br>\n  \u2014 Direct base classes for a single class [1 024].<br>\n  [...]<br>\n  \u2014 Direct and indirect virtual bases of a class [1 024].</br></br></br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'd say that's pretty generous.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "635608", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "20405380", "Score": "11", "CreationDate": "2013-12-05T16:29:25.720", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-05T16:29:25.720"}, "20405321": {"CommentCount": "4", "AcceptedAnswerId": "20405380", "CreationDate": "2013-12-05T16:26:41.440", "LastActivityDate": "2013-12-05T16:29:25.720", "PostTypeId": "1", "ViewCount": "1210", "FavoriteCount": "2", "Title": "Limit of multiple inheritance in C++", "Id": "20405321", "Score": "8", "Body": "<p>What is the limit of multiple inheritance in C++? i.e, how many classes can a class inherit from? Is it implementation dependent or is there a constraint placed on the number of classes you can inherit from in multiple inheritance?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><multiple-inheritance>", "OwnerUserId": "3056230", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_20405321_20405376_0": {"section_id": 6982, "quality": 0.8095238095238095, "length": 17}, "so_20405321_20405380_0": {"section_id": 47, "quality": 0.8235294117647058, "length": 14}}, "n3337": {"so_20405321_20405376_0": {"section_id": 6728, "quality": 0.8095238095238095, "length": 17}}, "n4659": {"so_20405321_20405376_0": {"section_id": 8480, "quality": 0.8095238095238095, "length": 17}, "so_20405321_20405380_0": {"section_id": 48, "quality": 0.8235294117647058, "length": 14}}}});